2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
4 tbsp Hummus
30 g Mixed Olives
1 unit(s) Carrot
0.17 cup Panko Breadcrumbs
113 g Spring Mix
1 tbsp Shawarma Spice Blend
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
2 unit(s) Tomato
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
2 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
2 tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
0.38 tsp Salt*
1.5 tbsp Oil*

Peel, then halve carrot lengthwise. Cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Peel, halve, then thinly slice onion.
Cut tomato into 1/2-inch pieces.
Drain, then roughly chop olives.
Peel, then mince or grate garlic.

Combine Beyond Meat® patties, panko, Shawarma Spice Blend, half the garlic and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt in a large bowl.
Roll mixture into 8 (16) equal-sized meatballs.

Add carrots and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to one side of a parchment-lined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Arrange Beyond Meat® meatballs on the other side of the baking sheet.
Roast in the middle of the oven until carrots are golden-brown and meatballs are cooked through, 10-12 min.**

Meanwhile, add onions, vinegar, 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water and 2 tsp (4 tsp) sugar to a small pot.
Season with salt. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat.
Once simmering, cook, stirring often, until sugar dissolves, 1-2 min.
Remove from heat. Transfer onions, including pickling liquid, to a medium bowl.

Add mayo, hummus, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic and 2 tsp (4 tsp) water to a small bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine. Set aside.
Whisk together 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) pickling liquid and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil in another large bowl.
Add spring mix and tomatoes, then toss to combine.

Drain pickled onion and discard remaining pickling liquid.
Divide salad between plates, then top with olives, carrots, Beyond Meat® meatballs and pickled onions.
Drizzle creamy hummus dressing over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, prepare and cook it the same way the recipe instructs you to prepare and cook the beef. Disregard tip to add an egg to mixture.